MELT butter in medium saucepan over medium heat. Add bell pepper, onion and cumin; cook for 3 to 4 minutes or until tender. Stir in broth, salsa and corn. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cook for 5 minutes. HEAT vegetable oil in medium skillet over medium-high heat. Add tortilla strips; cook, turning frequently with tongs, for 2 to 4 minutes or until light golden brown and crisp. Remove from skillet; place on paper towels to soak. SERVE in soup bowls. Top with tortilla strips, cheese and a dollop of sour cream.